The above passages from Cyprian and St. Ambrose maintain the same characteristics of rhetoric as those found in the writings of the Apostle Paul.

They are didactic throughout, and set forth, the one treating of the Sacrament‚ the other of the equality of the Holy Spirit with the Father and with the Son, cardinal principles in a terse and vigorous way. They are admirably adapted to teaching‚ and conform in all respects to the Submissa Dictio.
